When I couldn't get some macro stuff to work with WLA today I got<br />pretty annoyed and thought about what else I could try. I ended up<br />compiling binutils (2.16) for 65816. Later versions dropped<br />support completely, but &lt;=2.16 will do.<br /><br />The real problem is writing a linker script for the ld though. Not<br />only is the syntax rather cryptic, it's also probably not really <br />intended to be used with a layout like on the snes, i.e rom banking.<br /><br />Should anyone here have experience with this though, feel free<br />to give me some hints... :)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=83">gilligan</a> — Mon Feb 02, 2009 2:57 pm</p><hr />
